$ Windows: international settings

So-called *international settings* include
  • default language
  • → Windows/development/Internationalization/locale
  • keyboard layout

International settings are typically configured with
   • → Windows/PowerShell (international → Windows/PowerShell/language/module[module])
   • Windows setup answer files
   • Deployment Imaging Servicing and Management (DISM,  → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/Dism_exe[`dism.exe`]?)

{ Powershell cmdLet nouns #windows-intl-cmdlet

  → Windows/PowerShell cmdLet → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun[nouns] that can be used to manage a Windows installation's international settings include
  table { ll
    `culture` ☰ Culture for current → Windows/user-account[user account]
    `winAcceptLanguageFromLanguageListOptOut` ☰ → development/web/HTTP[HTTP] → development/web/HTTP/header[Accept Language] from the Language List opt-out setting (A → Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/automatic/true-false[boolean value] / current user account)
    `winCultureFromLanguageListOptOut` ☰ Opt-out setting for *culture* (aka user locale). A boolean value
    → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/winDefaultInputMethodOverride[`winDefaultInputMethodOverride`] ☰ Default input method override settting (current user account)
    → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/winHomeLocation[`winHomeLocation`] ☰ Windows *GeoID* home locatin setting for the current user account
    → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/winLanguageBarOption[`winLanguageBarOption`] ☰ Language bar mode and language bar type (current user account)
    → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/winSystemLocale[`winSystemLocale`] ☰ System-local settings (the language for non-→ development/Unicode programs) (current computer)
    `winUILanguageOverride` ☰ Windows GUI language overrdide (current user account)
    `winUserLanguageList` ☰ Language list (current user account)
  table }

}


sa:

  → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Control-Panel/International[`HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Control Panel\International`]

  → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/intl_cpl[`intl.cpl`]

  → Windows/settings
